{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require \"New Recipe\" labels on food products when new ingredients are added ",
        "additional_details": "This would flag up the changes and alert customers with allergies and intolerances that they should check the ingredients for changes.\r\n\r\nI have food intolerances and need to check product labels when purchasing a new food product. I, therefore, expect recipes to be the same each time I buy that product afterward.\r\n\r\nHowever, when a store changes the recipe, there is often no acknowledgement of this, meaning that, people with allergies and intolerance like me, may buy and eat something harmful to them without realising. A \"New Recipe\" label would alert us the ingredient changes.\r\n",
        "background": "Make a law so that UK shop customers are warned when there are changes to food product recipes by the use of a \"New Recipe\" label.",
